TOMORROW marks the 58th anniversary of the Sharpeville Massacre. The event that happened on 21 March 1960 is a distant memory for many but for those who survived the terrible day, it is still very real.  The People’s Paper recently drove with Agnes Tsoai (78), Elizabeth Chabeli (69), Selina Mnguni (81) and Abraham Mofokeng (78) to the old police station.There, apartheid police gunned down 69 people, including their loved ones, neighbours and residents.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjstCEEcp4jDkbO0LowCnEH1skcWr_BeR2PWqilVDaLpTtmeAtW1cec_MmwLK9iGu_9m028EDvfXyoJR2XO9GaTdDqzYwlLJgT_7B7fs7wR82aywh1LMKjP0NF9aMKzW20BeLesrnoj9NRbsi0brpySme1MhyJBfr215o1YKp6-8ChrzJ50BTttf0sn0MdqICyYct3J28PCEv1lxLW-5wPuB63KhuNuO82VOSCxgrKqaq37lw7a6Tsiu734--6pC3qPS2FtJFz-1StB5xKDfOU09RDBSZBHY\x26sai\x3dAMfl-YTHcCT1AqJzgkgXTiwTFt6yIbPOHdpCOO_Oj2JtZSDl75TT05aTvd95yCx6V4lLPz-LyLXLS6fUSV0xVN_4_E3jY5tcqbBaeGcOPFfxaw\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzFYg6wZiZ9CgEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
